A Sized List Datatype
---------------------

Lets cook up our own `List` data type from scratch:

\begin{code}
data List a = Emp
            | (:+:) a (List a)
              deriving (Eq, Ord, Show)
\end{code}

We can write a **measure** that logically represents
the *size*, i.e. number of elements of a `List`:

\begin{code}
{-@ measure size      :: List a -> Int
    size (Emp)        = 0
    size ((:+:) x xs) = 1 + size xs
  @-}

{-@ invariant {v:List a | 0 <= size v} @-}

{-@ type ListN a N  = {v:List a | size v = N} @-}
\end{code}


\begin{code}
length            :: List a -> Int
length Emp        = 0
length (x :+: xs) = 1 + length xs
\end{code}

such that the following type checks:

\begin{code}
l3     = 3 :+: l2

l2     = 2 :+: l1

l1     = 1 :+: l0

{-@ l0 :: { r:List Int | size r == 0 } @-}
l0     = Emp :: List Int
\end{code}


